qWat: QGIS Water Module

How to install
--------------

in your shell:

	$ git clone URL-to-this-module
	$ cd qWat
	$ 
	$ git submodule init
	$ git submodule update
	$ make
	$ 
	$ path_to_this_module=`pwd`
	$ cd ~/.qgis2/python/plugins
	$ ln -s "$path_to_this_module"/qgis-plugin
	$ 
	$ qgis &

Now go to the extensions menu and activate the qwat module.

Using the example project
-------------------------

You'll need to set up a postgres database first. Then in your shell:

	$ id
        uid=1000(THE_USER_THAT_WILL_RUN_QGIS) ...
	$ sudo su - postgres # change to the postgres user
	$ echo "CREATE DATABASE gwat" | psql 
	$ echo "GRANT CREATE on DATABASE qwat to THE_USER_THAT_WILL_RUN_QGIS;" | psql

now go to the 'data-model' directory and run the 'create_schemas.bash' script.

Now you should be able to connect to the qwat database with QGIS.

